# OpenSpec Universal Agent Directives (Applicable to Cursor, OpenCode, etc.)
ATTENTION ALL AI AGENTS (Cursor, OpenCode, Cline, Goose, etc.): You are operating in a highly restricted Control-Inversion Engineering Workflow.
You MUST report your progress to the local supervisor using `curl` whenever you complete a specific stage OR modify ANY files.
Do NOT proceed to the next stage unless the API returns an HTTP 200 OK. If you receive an HTTP 400 Bad Request, READ the rule violation feedback and correct your work before re-submitting.

## Reporting Endpoint
Your reporting endpoint is: http://127.0.0.1:38192/api/report

## Allowed Skills & Progress Reporting
You must invoke the progress reporter at the completion of these triggers:

- Skill: propose (起草需求与提案)
  Trigger: 完成 proposal.md 编写后
  Action: Run `curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:38192/api/report -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"skill_name":"propose","status":"completed","file_path":"<the_modified_file_path>"}'` and wait for 200 OK.

- Skill: validate (校验和细化规格)
  Trigger: 完成 specs/ 规格文件拆解后
  Action: Run `curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:38192/api/report -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"skill_name":"validate","status":"completed","file_path":"<the_modified_file_path>"}'` and wait for 200 OK.

- Skill: apply (编码与实现)
  Trigger: 完成 tasks.md 编码任务后
  Action: Run `curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:38192/api/report -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"skill_name":"apply","status":"completed","file_path":"<the_modified_file_path>"}'` and wait for 200 OK.

- Skill: archive (打包封卷)
  Trigger: 完成修改落盘后
  Action: Run `curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:38192/api/report -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"skill_name":"archive","status":"completed","file_path":"<the_modified_file_path>"}'` and wait for 200 OK.

- Skill: track (全局变更追踪 (Universal Tracker))
  Trigger: 无论由于何种任务或在何种阶段，只要您的动作导致了文件的新增、修改或删除，必须立刻上报此技能
  Action: Run `curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:38192/api/report -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"skill_name":"track","status":"completed","file_path":"<the_modified_file_path>"}'` and wait for 200 OK.

